|WKBNAME|000
    add_shield

|WKBSYNOPSIS|000
    |YK0void|000 |CKBadd_shield|000(|YK0int|000 |GKBiAmount|000)
    |YK0void|000 |CKBadd_shield|000(|YK0int|000 |GKBiAmount|000, |YK0int|000 |GKBiType|000)
    |YK0void|000 |CKBadd_shield|000(|YK0int|000 |GKBiAmount|000, |YK0int|000 |GKBiType|000,
        |YK0closure|000 |GKBcDepleted|000)

|WKBDESCRIPTION|000
    Increase a living creature/player's shield for damage

    |GKBiAmount|000 is the amount of damage being added to the shield [Required]

    |GKBiType|000 is an optional parameter (|YK0bitmask|000) specifying the type of
    damage the shield will block/absorb.  If not specified, this shield
    will block all types of damage. May be useful to check <types.h>

    |GKBcDepleted|000 optionally supplies a depletion callback and acts as the
    stable handle for the shield points it owns. Callback-owned points absorb
    before unowned points in the same shield pool. When those points reach zero,
    the closure is called with the protected living and damage type:

        |CKBfuncall|000(|GKBcDepleted|000, |GKBprotected_living|000, |GKBiType|000)

    The caller must retain and reuse the exact same closure for later top-ups,
    queries, and cleanup. Existing one- and two-argument callers remain unowned
    and retain their previous behavior.


    |CKBadd_shield|000() is defined in /secure/living.c

|WKBSEE ALSO|000
    |CKBset_shield|000(L), |CKBquery_shield|000(L),
    |CKBquery_shield_callback|000(L), |CKBclear_shield_callback|000(L),
    |CKBremove_shield|000(L)
